# EcoDispose Research

## Overview

This research was conducted to generate ideas for the EcoDispose system using secondary sources such as government guidance, cybersecurity frameworks, and existing recycling systems.

---

## Feature 1: Waste Classification

**Source:**  
https://www.gov.uk/guidance/waste-electrical-and-electronic-equipment-weee-how-to-classify  

**Key Finding:**  
"You must classify the waste your business produces before it is collected, disposed of or recovered."

### Purpose
This feature allows EcoDispose to categorise electronic devices before disposal, ensuring compliance with WEEE regulations.

### System Requirements
- Device categories (laptops, phones, etc.)
- Classification options (reuse, recycle, dispose)
- Hazard indicators

### Design Ideas
- Green colour scheme
- Simple icons
- Clean dashboard layout

### User Needs
- Fast data entry
- Clear classifications
- Easy access during audits

---

## Feature 2: Secure Wipe Confirmation

**Source:**  
https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/collection/device-security-guidance/managing-deployed-devices/erasing-devices  

**Key Finding:**  
"Simply deleting files is not enough."

### Purpose
Ensures devices are securely wiped before disposal.

### Benefits
- Protects sensitive data
- Prevents data breaches
- Supports GDPR compliance

### Design Ideas
- Security icons (locks/shields)
- Status indicators (complete/pending)

---

## Feature 3: Device Registration System

**Source:**  
https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/weee-evidence-and-national-protocols-guidance  

**Key Finding:**  
"Keep detailed and accurate records."

### Purpose
Tracks all devices entering the disposal process.

### Features
- Unique device ID
- Disposal tracking
- Record storage

### Design Ideas
- Database-style layout
- Tables and search functionality

---

## Conclusion

The research directly influenced the development of EcoDispose by defining its key features, user needs, and design principles.
